          <h3 class="header-small">How was this website made?</h3>

          <p class="text-small">Population Fact Finder was built using <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Open-source_software" target="_blank">free and open source software</a> by <a href="https://planninglabs.nyc" target="_blank">NYC Planning Labs</a> working closely with DCP's Population Division. Itâ€™s a single-page application (SPA) built using the <a href="https://www.emberjs.com/" target="_blank">Ember</a> JavaScript framework. The frontend application consumes a variety of APIs that serve map tiles, data, and content.</p>

          <p class="text-small">We make use of the <a href="http://foundation.zurb.com/" target="_blank">Foundation for Sites</a> framework for layout and styling. Web maps on the profiles are built using <a href="https://www.mapbox.com/mapbox-gl-js/api/" target="_blank">Mapbox GL</a>, creating smooth-scaling vector-based maps with intricate control of styling. Interactive charts are built using <a href="https://d3js.org/" target="_blank">D3.js</a>.</p>

